	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'd like to know what reads back on KeyOn and KeyOff registers of the sound DSP. I don't see it really doccumented. Anyone have a clue ?
<br />
<br />What about reading $7c (voice end). Are the bit here set only when a sample ends, or are they also set when a sample loops ?
<br />
<br />Also reading $x8 reads back enveloppe value. But reding $x9 is more obscure. Supposely, it reads the wave being played on the Xth channel, but aren't samples 16-bit ? Are the read affected by noise, enveloppe, echo and volume ?
<br />
<br />Another one I'd be curious : Is it possible to abuse the echo buffer to play additional non-BRR samples ? Has anyone ever tried such a thing before ?

		

